#### ZZ shape ####
the input for the smoothing routines (using RooKeysPDF)
is a small tree with the following format.

TTree*tree=new TTree("tree","tree");
tree->Branch("mass", &mass, "mass/D");
tree->Branch("weight", &weightNN, "weight/D");

mass   : is the mass of the candidate in GeV
weight : is the total weight of the event

the tree should contain all events passing the analysis selection
a separate file for each final stage (4mu,2e2mu,2mu2e,4e) should be provided

#### Signal interpolation ####
The mass points where the Higgs hypothesis is tested are :
        - 110-160 : 500 MeV steps
        - 160-290 : 2 GeV steps
        - 290-350 : 5 GeV steps
        - 350-400 : 10 GeV steps
        - 400-600 : 20 GeV steps                                                                                                                                                                                                             
===> vector of interpolated points 
std::vector<double> higgsMassesResult;
for(double mass=110.;mass<160;mass+=0.5)
 higgsMassesResult.push_back(mass);
for(double mass=160.;mass<290;mass+=2.)
 higgsMassesResult.push_back(mass);
for(double mass=290.;mass<350;mass+=5.)
 higgsMassesResult.push_back(mass);
for(double mass=350.;mass<400;mass+=10.)
 higgsMassesResult.push_back(mass);
for(double mass=400.;mass<=600;mass+=20.)
 higgsMassesResult.push_back(mass);

